<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40032e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40032e">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40032e"> 32(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> eat pulse</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;Some villagers near Benares,&rdquo; mentioned by Dr. D. J. Fleming in &ldquo;Building with India,&rdquo; &ldquo;said that they ate only once in two days for a month or two in the cold weather before the winter harvest, when they get the pulses and barley. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 38</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: In India, the paddy [rice] is husked in a mortar, and the rice cooked with Dolichos Lablab, Cicer arietinum, and other pulses, without the addition of salt. </mm> </dd></dl>
